"{\"uid\": \"washingtontimes.com-news-2024-aug-4-noah-lyles-wins-olympic-100-by-five-thousandths-of\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"SAINT-DENIS, France -Noah Lylespaced on the far end of the track, hands folded over the top of his head, wistfully looking up at a scoreboard that would, sooner or later, flash an answer he's been seeking over three sweat-soaked years.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 11, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999863576, \"rank\": 1.3829041063896834e-11, \"text\": \"SAINT-DENIS\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Was all that toil since the last Olympics - all the work on the practice track and in the weight room in the name of finding a centimeter here or a millisecond there - really going to be worth all the trouble?\", \"from\": 237, \"to\": 446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ten seconds passed, then 20.\", \"from\": 448, \"to\": 476, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, nearly 30.\", \"from\": 477, \"to\": 493, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And then, the answer popped up.\", \"from\": 494, \"to\": 525, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes,Lylesis the 100-meter champion at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 527, \"to\": 584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The World's Fastest Man.\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 609, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just not by very much.\", \"from\": 611, \"to\": 633, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The American showman edged out Jamaica's Kishane Thompson on Sunday by five-thousandths of a second - that's .005 of one tick of the clock - in a race for the ages.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 639, \"end\": 647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999173403520928, \"rank\": 7.833967048648077e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 666, \"end\": 673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 2.03191055624782e-12, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 684, \"end\": 692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9999895922297136, \"rank\": 1.0407878375271705e-05, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The final tally in this one:Lyles9.784 seconds, Thompson 9.789.\", \"from\": 801, \"to\": 864, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The new champion said that before he left for Paris, one of his physio guys ensured him this race would be a squeaker.\", \"from\": 866, \"to\": 984, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 912, \"end\": 917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5552240030924319e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He said, 'This is how close first and second are going to be,'\\\"Lylessaid as he pinched his thumb and his forefinger together so they were almost touching.\", \"from\": 986, \"to\": 1141, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I can not believe how right he was.\\\"\", \"from\": 1142, \"to\": 1179, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For perspective, the blink of an eye takes, on average, .1 second.\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1247, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That was 20 times longer than the gap between first and second.\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1311, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was so close, that when the sprinters crossed the line and the word \\\"Photo\\\" popped up next to the names ofLyles, Thompson and five others in the eight-man field,Lyleswalked over to the Jamaican and said \\\"I think you got the Olympics dog.\\\"\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1554, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1429, \"end\": 1437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9999895922297136, \"rank\": 1.0407878375271705e-05, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 1501, \"end\": 1509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9099192860003706, \"rank\": 0.09899857645059067, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thompson, who raced three lanes to the left ofLylesand had no clue where he was on the track, wasn't convinced.\", \"from\": 1556, \"to\": 1667, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1556, \"end\": 1564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9999895922297136, \"rank\": 1.0407878375271705e-05, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was, 'Wow, I am not even sure, because it was that close,'\\\" the Jamaican said.\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1750, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1736, \"end\": 1744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9099192860003706, \"rank\": 0.09899857645059067, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Time would tell.\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It always does.\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1784, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"WhenLyles' name came up first, he snatched his name tag off the front of his bib and held it to the sky.\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 1889, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Moments later, he shouted at the TV camera: \\\"America, I told you I got this!\\\"\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 1967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The first four racers were separated by less than .03.\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 2023, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The top seven all finished within .09 of each other.\", \"from\": 2024, \"to\": 2076, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"America's Fred Kerley came in third at 9.81.\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2088, \"end\": 2099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fred Kerley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's probably one of the most beautiful races I have been in,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2123, \"to\": 2197, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the photo finish, Kerley's orange shoe crossed the line before anyone, or anything.\", \"from\": 2199, \"to\": 2285, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it's the chest breaking the barrier that counts.Lyles' chest crossed first.\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2365, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was the closest 1-2 finish in the 100 since at least Moscow in 1980 - or maybe even ever.\", \"from\": 2367, \"to\": 2461, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2425, \"end\": 2431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4827667229055787e-14, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Back then, Britain's Allan Wells narrowly beat Silvio Leonard in an era when the electronic timers did not go into the thousandths of a second.\", \"from\": 2463, \"to\": 2606, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2474, \"end\": 2481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9933379061521227, \"rank\": 0.006706682693201891, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2484, \"end\": 2495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allan_Wells\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Allan Wells\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allan_Wells\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allan_Wells\"}, {\"begin\": 2510, \"end\": 2524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Silvio_Leonard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Silvio Leonard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Silvio_Leonard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Silvio_Leonard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The same was true in 1932, when Eddie Tolan won the Olympics' first ever photo finish.\", \"from\": 2607, \"to\": 2693, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2639, \"end\": 2650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddie_Tolan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eddie Tolan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddie_Tolan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddie_Tolan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lylesconceded that during the excruciating wait, he was pretty sure he had dipped his chest just a tad too soon.\", \"from\": 2695, \"to\": 2807, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dipping, it turns out, is one of the few things he does not work on over and over again at his training track in Florida.\", \"from\": 2808, \"to\": 2929, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2921, \"end\": 2928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"score\": 0.6858004248143378, \"rank\": 0.4572122910833664, \"text\": \"Florida\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But I would say I have a decent history with dipping,\\\" he said, recalling races he won in high school and as a junior.\", \"from\": 2931, \"to\": 3050, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 9.784 marked a new personal best forLylesand made him the first American champion in the marquee race at the Olympics since Justin Gatlin in 2004.\", \"from\": 3052, \"to\": 3202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3180, \"end\": 3193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Gatlin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Justin Gatlin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Gatlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Gatlin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lylesis hoping to go even bigger than that, and maybe take this sport back to a day when it was Carl Lewis and Edwin Moses lighting up the track - a must-see affair, the likes of whichLylesheadlined in front of around 80,000 on a warm night at the Stade de France.\", \"from\": 3204, \"to\": 3468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3300, \"end\": 3310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}, {\"begin\": 3315, \"end\": 3326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edwin_Moses\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Edwin Moses\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edwin_Moses\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edwin_Moses\"}, {\"begin\": 3452, \"end\": 3467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The mission started afterLylessettled for a bronze medal in Tokyo in his favorite - and then, only - sprint, the 200.\", \"from\": 3470, \"to\": 3587, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3530, \"end\": 3535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999996589395, \"rank\": 2.0086534864117008e-10, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those COVID-impacted Games were a terrible experience forLyles.\", \"from\": 3588, \"to\": 3651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He rededicated himself to bettering his mental health, but also looked for a new mission - the 100 meters and, with it, a chance at track immortality.\", \"from\": 3652, \"to\": 3802, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The practice was tough for a sprinter never known as a great starter, but he stuck with it.\", \"from\": 3804, \"to\": 3895, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When he won the world championships last year, then backed it up by winning the 200, his goal for Paris was very much in sight.\", \"from\": 3896, \"to\": 4023, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3994, \"end\": 3999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5552240030924319e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But when he came into the Olympic final having finished second in both his qualifying races and staring across at one sprinter who had run faster than him this year - Thompson - and another who had beaten him twice this year - Jamaica's Oblique Seville - he knew this would be no coronation.\", \"from\": 4025, \"to\": 4316, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4252, \"end\": 4259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 2.03191055624782e-12, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 4270, \"end\": 4277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seville\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.115863837254464e-12, \"text\": \"Seville\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seville\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seville\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thompson added another roadblock when, during the introduction, he let out a primal scream, the likes of whichLyleshas been unleashing in some of his biggest races.\", \"from\": 4318, \"to\": 4482, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4318, \"end\": 4326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9999895922297136, \"rank\": 1.0407878375271705e-05, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I thought 'Man, that's my thing, that's crazy,'\\\"Lylessaid.\", \"from\": 4484, \"to\": 4543, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lylesgalloped and leapt about 20 yards down the track before returning to the starting line, where the runners waited some three minutes for the gun to finally sound.\", \"from\": 4545, \"to\": 4711, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was worth the wait.\", \"from\": 4713, \"to\": 4735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, the question that could be debated for years is: What was the difference in this one?\", \"from\": 4737, \"to\": 4827, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Could it have been Lyles' closing speed and that lean into the line that he thought was mistimed?\", \"from\": 4829, \"to\": 4926, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4848, \"end\": 4853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9866829083873396, \"rank\": 0.013496138109652068, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Was it his ability to stay in reach of everyone among this straight line of sprinters over the first 60 meters - a skill he's been working on in tedious practice after practice since he took on the shorter sprint?\", \"from\": 4928, \"to\": 5141, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The answer: all that and more.\", \"from\": 5143, \"to\": 5173, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Everyone in the field came out knowing they could win this race,\\\"Lylessaid.\", \"from\": 5175, \"to\": 5251, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It took 9.784 seconds, then about 30 seconds more, for the scoreboard to flash the name of the man who actually did.\", \"from\": 5253, \"to\": 5369, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Seeing that name, I was like 'Oh my gosh, there it is!'\\\"Lylessaid.\", \"from\": 5371, \"to\": 5438, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold (and bronze) for Ukrainian high jumpers  Yaroslava Mahuchikh won Olympic gold in the high jump for her war-torn country of Ukraine and, as a bonus, had company.\", \"from\": 5440, \"to\": 5605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5462, \"end\": 5471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9994384152460208, \"rank\": 0.00055916291081713, \"text\": \"Ukrainian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 5486, \"end\": 5505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yaroslava_Mahuchikh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yaroslava Mahuchikh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yaroslava_Mahuchikh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yaroslava_Mahuchikh\"}, {\"begin\": 5568, \"end\": 5575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999634345109013, \"rank\": 3.5572362174764027e-05, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her teammate Iryna Gerashchenko won the bronze and the teammates hopped, skipped and jumped around the track parading their blue-and-yellow flags in a heartfelt celebration.\", \"from\": 5606, \"to\": 5779, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5625, \"end\": 5637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volodymyr_Herashchenko\", \"score\": 0.9951516416830872, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gerashchenko\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volodymyr_Herashchenko\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volodymyr_Herashchenko\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mahuchikh needed fewer tries to clear the winning height of 2 meters than Australia's Nicola Olyslagers, and so, added the sport's biggest prize of all - Olympic gold - to her world championship and world record.\", \"from\": 5781, \"to\": 5993, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5855, \"end\": 5864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9997916627836582, \"rank\": 0.00018527996268004308, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 5867, \"end\": 5873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicola_Roberts\", \"score\": 0.9999997077484722, \"rank\": 2.922512968502923e-07, \"text\": \"Nicola\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicola_Roberts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicola_Roberts\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kerr vs Ingebrigtsen is a go for heated men's 1,500  The best rivalry in track will culminate Tuesday when reigning world champion Josh Kerr of Britain takes on defending Olympic champion Jakob Ingebrigtsen of Norway.\", \"from\": 5995, \"to\": 6212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6126, \"end\": 6130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Madden\", \"score\": 0.999688344372731, \"rank\": 0.00026179794543949696, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Madden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Madden\"}, {\"begin\": 6139, \"end\": 6146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9933379061521227, \"rank\": 0.006706682693201891, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 6183, \"end\": 6201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jakob Ingebrigtsen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\"}, {\"begin\": 6205, \"end\": 6211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9819428939626366, \"rank\": 0.01832491672777533, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They squared off in Sunday's semifinal, too, and Ingebrigtsen edged out the Brit, looking over to him twice as they surged down the homestretch, to win a race that felt like it meant more than it should have in 3:32.38.\", \"from\": 6214, \"to\": 6433, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They should be expecting one of the most vicious and hardest 1,500s the sport's seen in a very long time,\\\" Kerr said.\", \"from\": 6435, \"to\": 6553, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Did Ingebrigtsen agree?\", \"from\": 6555, \"to\": 6578, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Depends who you ask, maybe,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 6580, \"to\": 6618, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I mean, racing is what you want it to be.\\\"\", \"from\": 6619, \"to\": 6662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2025 The Washington Times, LLC.\", \"from\": 6664, \"to\": 6707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6703, \"end\": 6706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"score\": 0.9999406342231656, \"rank\": 5.9369301329320356e-05, \"text\": \"LLC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Limited_liability_company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SEE MORE VIDEOS  Where's Islamic extremism in National Guard shooting discussion?\", \"from\": 6709, \"to\": 6790, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6734, \"end\": 6751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_terrorism\", \"score\": 0.6622870939667144, \"rank\": 0.5091667622062883, \"text\": \"Islamic extremism\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_terrorism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islamic_terrorism\"}, {\"begin\": 6755, \"end\": 6769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Guard_of_Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999750864101151, \"rank\": 2.2992469459191498e